The legal showdown between Please Call Me inventor Nkosana Makate and Vodacom is far from over. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The legal showdown between Please Call Me inventor Nkosana Makate and Vodacom is far from over. Makate this week scored a key victory in the Gauteng division of the High Court when Judge Kollapen ordered the cellphone giant to furnish Makate's legal team with key documents. READ:Â Vodacom data prices will fall The documents include contracts Vodacom entered into with providers of so-called Value Added Services, as well as data behind the company's revenue records. This case is separate, but linked, to his main court challenge to the Vodacom CEO's determination that his compensation for introducing the service in 2000, must be R47-million.